The paper discusses citation networks and their use in scientific evaluation and science mapping, which are topics related to information science (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The paper also discusses interdisciplinary studies and the behavior of citation impacts across scientific fields, which are topics related to social informatics (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of growth rate and balance as measures, which are topics related to system dynamics (cs.SD).
